  "body": "Currently CIDRAllocator observes only Node creations and deletions. When Node is created it tries to assign a CIDR to it. If it fails for any reason (no available CIDRs, run out of Node update retries) it won't ever retry, as the Node won't be \"created\" again. We need to add a mechanism for retrying assignments in such cases.\n\ncc @kubernetes/goog-control-plane \n",
